<Grid RowColumns="RowColumns.Are1" Border="Border.Rounded" Margin="Margin.Is4.OnX" Shadow="Shadow.Default"
    Padding="Padding.Is4.OnY">
    <Column ColumnSize="ColumnSize.IsFull" Margin="Margin.Is4.OnX">
        <InfoHeading TextPadding="Padding.Is4.OnY">GENERAL INFORMATION</InfoHeading>

        <InfoList>
            <InfoListItem>
                The tournament will be held on <b>August 2-4 at the WFCU Centre</b> (8787 McHugh St.)
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                Players <b>must be registered prior to the draft</b> (date TBA) in order to play
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                There is a <b>$50 registration fee</b>. This fee covers ice, refs, timekeepers and prizes
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                There will be four teams, each with an assigned team captain
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                Teams will be drafted by their respective captains a few days prior to the first game
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                Each team is <b>guaranteed four games</b>
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                Each game will start with a <b>3-minute warmup</b> and will have <b>three 12-minute stop-time
                    periods</b>.
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                The first three games are round-robin. Teams will be seeded based on their records. If teams finish with
                the same records, the tie-breaker will be determined in the following order
                <OrderedList>
                    <OrderedListItem>
                        Head-to-head result
                    </OrderedListItem>
                    <OrderedListItem>
                        Goal differential
                    </OrderedListItem>
                    <OrderedListItem>
                        Goals scored
                    </OrderedListItem>
                </OrderedList>
                After the round-robin games, the finals will take place on Sunday (1st vs 2nd, 3rd vs 4th).
            </InfoListItem>
            <InfoListItem>
                There will be prizes awarded to the winning teams
            </InfoListItem>
        </InfoList>

    </Column>
</Grid>
